documentation:
Empty \_\_classinit\_\_ implementation.

This must be a no-op as subclasses can't reliably call base class's
\_\_classinit\_\_ from their \_\_classinit\_\_s.

Subclasses of \_\_classinit\_\_ should look like:

```
.. python::

    class MyClass(ClassInitBase):

        @classmethod
        def __classinit__(cls):
            # Need globals().get as MyClass may be still undefined.
            super(globals().get('MyClass', cls),
                    cls).__classinit__()
            ...

    class Derived(MyClass):

        @classmethod
        def __classinit__(cls):
            super(globals().get('Derived', cls),
                    cls).__classinit__()
            ...
```
